over bond sales and repurchase agreements, ultimately requiring DG Bank to
take heavy write-offs.
DG Bank would only confirm yesterday, in response to an article in the
Spiegel news magazine, that the investigation was under way and had been
approved by management and supervisory boards.
In October last year, Mr Bernd Thiemann, the bank's chief executive since
early 1991, announced a DM1.4bn (Dollars 840m) cash injection and said the
bank would only break even at the operating level.
