<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 92 / International Company News: American Express and Banamex
deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAMIAN FRASER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN Express and Banamex, Mexico's largest bank, have formed a joint
venture, known as Banamsa, to provide financial services to the fast-growing
Mexican market, writes Damian Fraser.
The new company will start by offering in Mexico an American Express gold
card, co-branded with the Banamex name. Mr Roberto Hernandez, the president
of Banamex, hoped 500,000 customers would subscribe to the card within three
years. Banamex will market the new card in its 725 branches.
