FT  02 MAR 92 / Ukraine takes step towards own currency
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRYSTIA FREELAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Russian rouble yesterday ceased to be accepted by the Ukrainian state
sector for cash transactions. Salaries are to be paid primarily in Ukrainian
coupons - which have effectively become a separate currency - and all
purchases from state sectors must be made through coupons or rouble savings
in bank accounts.
Ukrainian media announced over the weekend that as of March 1, 75 per cent
of wages will be paid in coupons and the remainder will be deposited in
workers' rouble bank accounts. All purchases in the state shops of less than
Rbs4,000 are to be made in coupons. Larger transactions cannot be made in
cash, but must be paid through bank transfers. Moreover, the wholesale
sector is to switch to coupons.
The measures are a reaction to Ukraine's critical shortage of roubles and
are in preparation for the introduction of a fully separate Ukrainian
currency, the hryvnia, scheduled for this summer.
</TEXT>
